\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces HCCP at a glance. \textbf  {(a)} A heteroscedastic aggregator produces a point estimate $\hat  {p}(x)$ and a learned variance $\hat  {\sigma }(x)$; the nonconformity score $s(x,y) = |y - \hat  {p}(x)| / \hat  {\sigma }(x)$ scales the decision radius by local uncertainty. \textbf  {(b)} Mondrian calibration partitions the labeled data by $(y \times \hat  {\sigma }\text  {-bin})$; per-cell quantile thresholds $\hat  {q}_{k,b}$ restore both class-conditional (T2) and bin-conditional (T3) coverage, while remaining compatible with Barber's \citep  {barber2020limits} pointwise impossibility. \textbf  {(c)} Three-axis OOD stress tests --- chromosome-LOO, trait-LOO, cross-dataset --- verify that the $\hat  {\sigma }$-bin coverage gap reaches the finite-sample floor $0.002$--$0.004$ under trait-LOO and stays $\leq 0.077$ across chromosome-LOO and the C$\to $M cross-dataset direction on TraitGym; the M$\to $C cross-dataset direction is reported as an honest limitation.}}{2}{figure.1}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:concept}{{1}{2}{HCCP at a glance. \textbf {(a)} A heteroscedastic aggregator produces a point estimate $\phat (x)$ and a learned variance $\shat (x)$; the nonconformity score $s(x,y) = |y - \phat (x)| / \shat (x)$ scales the decision radius by local uncertainty. \textbf {(b)} Mondrian calibration partitions the labeled data by $(y \times \shat \text {-bin})$; per-cell quantile thresholds $\qhat _{k,b}$ restore both class-conditional (T2) and bin-conditional (T3) coverage, while remaining compatible with Barber's \citep {barber2020limits} pointwise impossibility. \textbf {(c)} Three-axis OOD stress tests --- chromosome-LOO, trait-LOO, cross-dataset --- verify that the $\shat $-bin coverage gap reaches the finite-sample floor $0.002$--$0.004$ under trait-LOO and stays $\leq 0.077$ across chromosome-LOO and the C$\to $M cross-dataset direction on TraitGym; the M$\to $C cross-dataset direction is reported as an honest limitation}{figure.1}{}}
