\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {5}{\ignorespaces HCCP $\hat  {\sigma }$-bin gap across three OOD axes (log scale). Trait-LOO reaches the finite-sample $1/(n_{k,b}+1)$ floor on both datasets; chrom-LOO and cross-dataset (C$\to $M only; M$\to $C shown in Tab.\nobreakspace  {}\ref  {tab:threeaxis}) sit under the $0.04$ headline threshold in all cases except the Complex cross-dataset column, whose violation is diagnostic of the shift direction rather than of HCCP.}}{16}{figure.5}\protected@file@percent }
